3 SENATE BILL NO. 1632 By: Alvord
4
5
6 An Act relating to schools; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 14-135, which relates to career-readiness
7 assessments; directing the State Department of
Education, rather than the Oklahoma Department of
8 Commerce, in certain cooperation to approve certain
assessments and credentials; removing language making
9 such approval subject to funding; directing the
assessments to be made available to students in
10 certain grades beginning in certain school year;
directing the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher
11 Education in certain consultation to promulgate
certain rules; providing an effective date; and
12 declaring an emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 14-135, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 14-135. Subject to the availability of funds, beginning
19 with the 2019-2020 school year, the Oklahoma Department of Commerce,
20 in cooperation with the
21 A. The State Department of Education and, in cooperation with
22 the Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability, shall
23 review and approve career-readiness assessments and assessment-based
24 credentials that measure and document foundational workplace skills.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1632 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Begi nning with the 2019-2020 2026-2027 school year, the assessments
2 shall be made available to all public school districts to be
3 administered to students at the discretion of each school district’s
4 administration to students in grades ten through twelve at least
5 once prior to their graduation from high school. The assessment-
6 based credential shall be available to any student who achieves the
7 prescribed level on the required assessments assessment. If the
8 public school district chooses to administer the assessments, the
9 assessments shall be administered at least once to each student who
10 chooses to take the assessment at no cost to the student. The
11 assessments shall:
12 1. Be a standardized, criterion-referenced measure of broadly
13 relevant foundational workplace skills;
14 2. Assess and document student readiness for a wide range of
15 jobs;
16 3. Measure skills in the following areas, including, but not
17 limited to:
18 a. applied mathematics,
19 b. workplace documents,
20 c. graphic literacy, or
21 d. critical thinking and leadership collaboration;
22 4. Align with research-based skill requirement profiles for
23 specific industries and occupations;
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1632 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 5. Lead to nationally recognized work-readiness certificates or
2 credentials for students who meet the minimum proficiency
3 requirements on the component assessments; and
4 6. Be available in paper- and computer-based formats.
5 B. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education, in
6 consultation with the American Council on Education National Guide,
7 shall promulgate rules to allow institutions of higher education
8 within The Oklahoma State System of Higher Education to grant
9 college credit based on assessment-based credentials and scores
10 earned on career-readiness assessments.
11 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
12 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
13 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
14 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
15 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
16 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION
